TY  - JOUR
AU  - Carr, Peter
AU  - Wu, Liuren
T1  - Decomposing Long Bond Returns: A Decentralized Theory*
PY  - 2023
Y1  - 2023/05/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfac053
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 27
IS  - 3
SP  - 997
EP  - 1026
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - Classic bond pricing centralizes bond valuation across all maturities by specifying the dynamics of the short-term interest rate. This article develops a decentralized theory that prices each bond based purely on the near-term behavior of the bond’s own yield. The theory levers the domain expertise of an investor on a particular bond and allows the investor to make pricing and investment analysis on the bond without the shackles of an ambitious centralizing mandate. The theory decomposes the short-term return on a bond with respect to the variation of its own yield. Imposing no dynamic arbitrage on the return decomposition leads to a simple pricing equation relating the bond yield to the market pricing and conditional mean and variance forecasts of the yield’s near-term change. The article illustrates the theory’s applications in decentralized investment of a single bond and in the construction and investment of decentralized butterfly bond portfolios.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfac053
ER  - 



