AU  - Sulaeman, Johan
AU  - Yan, Jubo
AU  - Zhang, Jialiang
T1  - Expanding Footprints: The Impact of Passenger Transportation on Corporate Locations*
PY  - 2023
Y1  - 2023/05/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfac049
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 27
IS  - 3
SP  - 1119
EP  - 1154
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - This article investigates how transportation networks shape firms’ geographic footprint by reducing monitoring costs of distant investments. Exploiting the staggered expansions of China’s passenger high-speed rail (HSR) network, we document that the amount of intercity investment between a pair of cities increases by 45% with the introduction of an HSR line connecting the cities. We enhance the causal inference by applying high-dimensional fixed effects, and focusing on city pairs that are “accidentally” connected in the network. The HSR effect is the strongest in industries that require on-site monitoring, as well as for controlling stakes in large distant investments.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfac049
ER  - 



